M
with a new conditional distribution ÀÜpt := P ÀÜ
M(x)[yt = ¬∑|y1:t‚àí1] on V. Additionally, it outputs a detection
key k associated with
ÀÜ
M. The watermark could contain certain randomness.
‚Ä¢ Detect(k, y): This algorithm takes input detection key k and sequence y, then outputs 1 (indicating it was
generated by
ÀÜ
M) or 0 (indicating it was not generated by
ÀÜ
M).
We require the following three correctness properties to hold:
