privacy literature [Dwork et al., 2006, Dong et al., 2020].
Remark 3.2 (KL-divergence and other probability distance metrics). Renyi-divergence is very general.
Kullback-Leibler-divergence and chi-square divergence are directly implied by the Œ±-Renyi divergence bound
of min{Œ¥, Œ±Œ¥2/8} by choosing Œ± = 1 and Œ± = 2 respectively and swap ÀÜp and p. Hellinger distance can
be obtained by choosing Œ± = 0.5.
