drawn from the original (un-watermarked) language model M.
For convenience, we define the following shorthand p(G) := Py‚àºp[y ‚àà G]. for a probability mass function p
defined on the vocabulary V. Specifically, ÀÜpt(G|ÀÜy1:t‚àí1) means Py‚àºÀÜpt(¬∑|x,ÀÜy1:t‚àí1)[y ‚àà G], parameterized by a
fixed green list G. Similarly, pt(G|y1:t‚àí1) denotes Py‚àºpt(¬∑|x,y1:t‚àí1)[y ‚àà G].
The proof of Theorem C.13 considers the following decomposition
