alternative roll-out y1:t‚àí1 sampled under M(x) (or p).
3. Then we control Term (7) by first Taylor expanding it into quantities involving pt(G|y1:t‚àí1) instead of
ÀÜp(G|y1:t‚àí1), then apply concentration inequalities for each expanded terms over the randomness of G
(while fixing y1:t‚àí1) to obtain a high probability lower bound. Proposition C.19 gives the results.
