Definition F.3 (Martingale). A sequence of random variables (Xn)n‚ààN is called a martingale if it satisfies
the following conditions:
1. E[|Xn|] < ‚àû for all n ‚àà N.
2. E[Xn+1|Fn] = Xn for all n ‚àà N.
where F1 ‚äÜ F2 ‚äÜ ... ‚äÜ Fn ‚äÜ Fn+1 ‚äÜ ... is a filtration. Specifically, Fn can be the sigma-algebra generated by
another sequence of random variable Y1, ..., Yn, i.e., Fn = œÉ(Y1:n) and Xn can be a function of Y1:n.
